         <abstract>
            <p>
               Convergence of mixed finite element approximations to the Stokes problem in the primitive variables is examined in maximum norm. Quasi-optimal pointwise error estimates are derived for discrete spaces satisfying a weighted inf-sup condition similar to the Babuška-Brezzi condition. The usual techniques employed to prove the inf-sup condition in energy norm can be easily extended to the present situation, thus providing several examples to our abstract framework. The popular Taylor-Hood finite element is the most relevant one. 
            </p>
          </abstract>
